# Wax | Wane — Cursor Rules
# This file tells Cursor how to behave for ALL code and automation in this project.
# Read docs/TONE_OF_VOICE.md and docs/AUTOMATION_ARCHITECTURE.md before doing anything.

## Identity
You are building automations and tools for Samantha, the founder of Wax | Wane (waxandwane.store)
and LNK.Nebraska (lnknebraska.com). She is a solo entrepreneur managing multiple brands and sales
channels. Your job is to make her life simpler, not more complicated.

## Non-Negotiable Rules

### Content & Tone
- Always use Title Case for headlines and product titles.
- Crystal descriptions use Gemini-style grade callouts: Collector Grade, Prism Grade, Rare Grade, Museum Quality.
- Never make direct medical or healing claims. Use "associated with," "crystal lore suggests," etc.
- Amazon bullet points: ALL CAPS LABEL: normal text description.
- Natural variation in crystals is always a feature, never a flaw. Include a disclaimer.
- Read docs/TONE_OF_VOICE.md for the full style guide.

### Automation Architecture
- Shopify is the single source of truth. All generated content must be written back as Shopify metafields.
- All n8n automations built by AI agents must be prefixed with "MANUS" in their workflow name.
- Always validate URLs before including them in social media posts.
- Read docs/AUTOMATION_ARCHITECTURE.md for the full system design.

### Secrets & Credentials
- NEVER hardcode secrets in code files. Use environment variables.
- Secret names follow the pattern in config-vault/registry/credentials.yaml (see wax-wane/config-vault repo).
- Shopify store: 6f97d0.myshopify.com
- Primary Shopify Admin API token env var: WAX_WANE_SHOPIFY_TOKEN (may need refresh)
- Veeqo API token env var: VEEQO_API_KEY (may need refresh)
- OpenAI API key env var: OPENAI_API_KEY
- Veeqo Channel IDs: Walmart=1009103, TikTok=1044457, Amazon=1049861, Etsy=1049903
- Facebook Page ID: 203171376205580
- Facebook Catalog ID: 1162102955270557

