### Code Style
- Python: use requests library, always handle errors gracefully, log results to JSON files.
- JavaScript/Node: use fetch or axios, async/await pattern.
- n8n workflows: use Code nodes for data transformation, HTTP Request nodes for API calls.
- Always add comments explaining what each section does.
- Save scripts to files, never run inline.

## When Tokens/Keys Look Stale
If an API call returns 401 or 403, note it as a "stale credential" and continue with other tasks.
Do NOT delete old tokens — they serve as a reference for what key names to use when refreshed.
The secondary/fallback tokens are documented in the registry; try them before declaring a credential dead.

## Project Structure
- n8n-workflows/ — importable n8n JSON workflow files
- docs/ — tone of voice, architecture, and setup guides
- scripts/ — utility scripts (Python, shell)
- .cursorrules — this file
